<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  NIL VPN — container app entitlements (bundle id: com.nilvpn.client).

  This is integration scaffolding. It CANNOT be compiled, signed, or run in this
  environment (no Xcode, no developer-mode Mac, no Apple Developer account).
  Signing these for real requires a paid Apple Developer ID plus matching
  provisioning profiles that grant the Network Extension capability — a deferred
  milestone, not something that can be produced here.

  Privacy note (NIL SOUL): entitlements declare OS capabilities only. They carry
  no identity. No node address, token, grant, or measurement appears in any
  entitlement or config — those cross into the System Extension at runtime via
  providerConfiguration and are never logged (PD-2, PD-3).

  Keys, and why each is here:

  * com.apple.developer.networking.networkextension
      Declares the app uses Network Extension, scoped to
      `packet-tunnel-provider-systemextension`: an NEPacketTunnelProvider packaged
      as a macOS *system extension* (not the older app-extension form). The app
      needs this to create/manage an NETunnelProviderManager and to activate the
      System Extension that runs the tunnel. Requires Apple org approval of the
      Network Extension capability on the signing account.

  * com.apple.developer.system-extension.install
      Lets the container app submit an OSSystemExtensionRequest.activationRequest
      to install and request approval of the bundled System Extension. This key
      is on the APP only (the extension itself does not install anything). The
      one-time user approval lands in System Settings > General > Login Items &
      Extensions.

  * com.apple.security.application-groups
      Shared App Group `group.com.nilvpn.client`, the only sanctioned channel
      between the app and its System Extension. Both targets must declare the
      identical group for shared container access to work.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>com.apple.developer.networking.networkextension</key>
	<array>
		<string>packet-tunnel-provider-systemextension</string>
	</array>
	<key>com.apple.developer.system-extension.install</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.application-groups</key>
	<array>
		<string>group.com.nilvpn.client</string>
	</array>
</dict>
</plist>
